<subSubSection id="C36CDFB78A14BC1E7D88FE38FEEDFE74" pageId="6" pageNumber="43" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BC98C3C8A14BC1E7D88FE38FEEDFE74" blockId="6.[151,1436,261,922]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis id="B902502E8A14BC1E7D88FE38FEA7FE3F" bold="true" box="[198,339,410,436]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name refers to the vessel, HM Bark 
<taxonomicName id="4C76F7BF8A14BC1E7EF0FE38FBCAFE38" authorityName="Lowry &amp; Stoddart" authorityYear="2010" box="[958,1086,410,435]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hirondelleidae" genus="Hirondellea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="endeavour">
<emphasis id="B902502E8A14BC1E7EF0FE38FBCAFE38" box="[958,1086,410,435]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">Endeavour</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, on which Lieutenant James Cook was sailing when he named the nearest point to the 
<typeStatus id="54CD329E8A14BC1E7E3EFE62FC51FE51" box="[880,933,448,474]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">type</typeStatus>
locality, Point Hicks; used as a noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36CDFB78A14BC1E7D88FDA8FA6FFD31" pageId="6" pageNumber="43" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BC98C3C8A14BC1E7D88FDA8FA6FFD31" blockId="6.[151,1436,261,922]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis id="B902502E8A14BC1E7D88FDA8FEB2FDAF" bold="true" box="[198,326,522,548]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B902502E8A14BC1E7C00FDA8FE7AFDA8" box="[334,398,522,547]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">Head</emphasis>
lobe broadly subtriangular. 
<emphasis id="B902502E8A14BC1E7F92FDA8FCBDFDA8" box="[732,841,522,547]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">Epistome</emphasis>
strongly produced, subtriangular with acute apex. 
<emphasis id="B902502E8A14BC1E7DD9FD92FEC0FDC2" box="[151,308,560,585]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">Gnathopod 1</emphasis>
propodus palm transverse, straight; dactylus slightly over-reaching palm, with 1 subterminal spine on inner margin. 
<emphasis id="B902502E8A14BC1E7CF3FDF7FD96FDE5" box="[445,610,597,622]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">Gnathopod 2</emphasis>
minutely subchelate; propodus length 2.2 × breadth. 
<emphasis id="B902502E8A14BC1E7844FDF7FA68FDE5" box="[1290,1436,597,622]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">Epimeron 1</emphasis>
anteroventral corner rounded. 
<emphasis id="B902502E8A14BC1E7F4AFDD8FD64FD18" box="[516,656,634,659]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">Epimeron 3</emphasis>
posteroventral corner produced into large spine. 
<emphasis id="B902502E8A14BC1E79ADFDD8FAA1FD18" box="[1251,1365,634,659]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">Uropod 2</emphasis>
inner ramus not incised. 
<emphasis id="B902502E8A14BC1E7C3DFD02FE17FD32" box="[371,483,672,697]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">Uropod 3</emphasis>
outer ramus article 2 long, 0.6 × article 1. 
<taxonomicName id="4C76F7BF8A14BC1E7E9CFD02FBE9FD32" authorityName="Pearse" authorityYear="1952" box="[978,1053,672,697]" class="Hexanauplia" family="Telsidae" genus="Telson" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="6" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B902502E8A14BC1E7E9CFD02FBE9FD32" box="[978,1053,672,697]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">Telson</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
length 1.2 × breadth, cleft 38 %.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36CDFB78A14BC1E7D88FD67FDA4FCFF" pageId="6" pageNumber="43" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC98C3C8A14BC1E7D88FD67FDA4FCFF" blockId="6.[151,1436,261,922]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis id="B902502E8A14BC1E7D88FD67FECBFD54" bold="true" box="[198,319,709,735]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C76F7BF8A14BC1E7C00FD67FD91FD55" authorityName="Lowry &amp; Stoddart" authorityYear="2010" box="[334,613,709,734]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hirondelleidae" genus="Hirondellea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="endeavour">
<emphasis id="B902502E8A14BC1E7C00FD67FD91FD55" box="[334,613,709,734]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">Hirondellea endeavour</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only known Australian species with a transverse palm on gnathopod 1. However, 
<taxonomicName id="4C76F7BF8A14BC1E7CFCFD48FDB6FC88" baseAuthorityName="Stephensen" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[434,578,746,771]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hirondelleidae" genus="Hirondellea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abyssalis">
<emphasis id="B902502E8A14BC1E7CFCFD48FDB6FC88" box="[434,578,746,771]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">H. abyssalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C76F7BF8A14BC1E7F1FFD48FD19FC88" baseAuthorityName="Schellenberg" baseAuthorityYear="1926" box="[593,749,746,771]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hirondelleidae" genus="Hirondellea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antarctica">
<emphasis id="B902502E8A14BC1E7F1FFD48FD19FC88" box="[593,749,746,771]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">H. antarctica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C76F7BF8A14BC1E7FB3FD48FC4EFC88" authorityName="Chevreux" authorityYear="1910" box="[765,954,746,771]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hirondelleidae" genus="Hirondellea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicaudata">
<emphasis id="B902502E8A14BC1E7FB3FD48FC4EFC88" box="[765,954,746,771]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">H. brevicaudata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C76F7BF8A14BC1E7EBBFD48FB97FC88" authorityName="Barnard &amp; Ingram" authorityYear="1990" box="[1013,1123,746,771]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hirondelleidae" genus="Hirondellea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guyoti">
<emphasis id="B902502E8A14BC1E7EBBFD48FB97FC88" box="[1013,1123,746,771]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">H. guyoti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
all have transverse palms. 
<taxonomicName id="4C76F7BF8A14BC1E7DD9FCB2FE44FCA2" authorityName="Lowry &amp; Stoddart" authorityYear="2010" box="[151,432,784,809]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hirondelleidae" genus="Hirondellea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="endeavour">
<emphasis id="B902502E8A14BC1E7DD9FCB2FE44FCA2" box="[151,432,784,809]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">Hirondellea endeavour</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shares a non-constricted uropod 2 inner ramus and a medium cleft telson with 
<taxonomicName id="4C76F7BF8A14BC1E7831FCB2FEF6FCC5" baseAuthorityName="Stephensen" baseAuthorityYear="1923" class="Malacostraca" family="Hirondelleidae" genus="Hirondellea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abyssalis">
<emphasis id="B902502E8A14BC1E7831FCB2FEF6FCC5" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">H. abyssalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C76F7BF8A14BC1E7C75FC97FE0CFCC5" authorityName="Chevreux" authorityYear="1910" box="[315,504,821,846]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hirondelleidae" genus="Hirondellea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicaudata">
<emphasis id="B902502E8A14BC1E7C75FC97FE0CFCC5" box="[315,504,821,846]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">H. brevicaudata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It differs from both of these species in the posteroventral corner of epimeron 3 which is developed into a large spine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36CDFB78A14BC1E7D88FCDDFCA4FC11" box="[198,848,895,922]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BC98C3C8A14BC1E7D88FCDDFCA4FC11" blockId="6.[151,1436,261,922]" box="[198,848,895,922]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis id="B902502E8A14BC1E7D88FCDDFE93FC12" bold="true" box="[198,359,895,921]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">Distribution.</emphasis>
South-eastern 
<collectingCountry id="F361CCAC8A14BC1E7F58FC22FD75FC11" box="[534,641,896,922]" name="Australia" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">Australia</collectingCountry>
in 
<quantity id="4C8E21D98A14BC1E7FE9FC22FCF4FC11" box="[679,768,896,922]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8399999999999999" pageId="6" pageNumber="43" unit="m" value="1840.0">1840 m</quantity>
depth.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
